<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP21_ProjectGold_NobleCareer_Favor" s="489799">
  <T n="category">488441<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_EP21_ProjectGold--></T>
  <T n="name">0x66B4F7B2<!--String: "Noble Favor"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_NobleCareer_Favor1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d604b00f4e600a12</T>
      <T n="text">0x476EB0B7<!--String: "Building your reputation as a Noble is important to show where your leadership priorities lie. Sims in the Noble Career will start out with a Neutral Favor alignment. \n\nNobles can be either <b><font color='#199C2C'>Commoner Favored</font></b> or <b><font color='#199C2C'>Royalty Favored</font></b> depending on the actions they take. You can view your alignment in the Career panel. \n\nDepending on both your own and another Sim's Favor, it may mean they are more likely to build faster relationships or react negatively if their Favors conflict."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_NobleCareer_Favor2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:d604b00f4e600a11</T>
      <T n="text">0xDD845557<!--String: "Sims can earn Favor through certain career interactions. You can <b><font color='#199C2C'>Reply to Noble Mail</font></b>, go on a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Noble Venture</font></b>, <b><font color='#199C2C'>Set Taxes</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Donate to the Kingdom</font></b>.\n\nSims can also build favor through social interactions, with more opportunities becoming available as they reach higher Favor levels.\n\nKeep an eye out for <b><font color='#199C2C'>Noble Gifts</font></b>, which are delivered every few days. Depending on the sender's own Favor alignment your Sim may receive a lovely present or something not so nice!\n"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
